<% content_for :title, "Become a Hanakai sponsor" %>

<div class="lg:mt-8 lg:mb-14">
  <header class="mb-12">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold mb-4">
      Sponsor Hanakai. Help us build a diverse future for Ruby.
    </h1>
  </header>

  <div class="space-y-12">
    <aside>
      <p>
        For more than a decade, Hanami, Dry and Rom have offered Ruby developers
        something different: tools built around clarity, flexibility, and a
        genuine belief that there's more than one good way to build an app. This
        year we've brought all three together under Hanakai, a unified project
        with a shared community and future. We've delivered on this. Now comes
        the part where we make it last.
      </p>

      <p>
        Sustaining Hanakai means steady, ongoing work: releasing gems, improving
        your developer experience, and growing our community. This needs me to
        show up consistently, over the long run. And beyond that, we want more of
        our maintainers to get the recognition and compensation they deserve.
      </p>

      <p>
        Ruby is a better place when there are real alternatives to reach for. If
        you believe this — or if Dry, Rom or Hanami are already doing important
        work somewhere in your stack — sponsorship is how you grow Hanakai and
        Ruby's diversity along with it.
      </p>

      <p>
        — Tim Riley<br>
        Hanakai project lead
      </p>
    </aside>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">How we use your money</h2>

      <p class="mb-4">Every dollar goes directly to sustaining Hanakai:</p>

      <ul class="space-y-2 mb-4">
        <li><strong>Up to $30k/year</strong> funds one day a week of Tim's time, as lead maintainer.</li>
        <li><strong>$30–40k/year</strong> builds a reserve for community and promotional activities.</li>
        <li><strong>Beyond $40k/year</strong> pays additional Hanakai maintainers for their ongoing work.</li>
      </ul>

      <p>We are currently supported at $26k/year.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">How to sponsor us</h2>

      <p>
        You can sponsor us via
        <a href="https://opencollective.com/hanami">Open Collective</a>
        or
        <a href="https://github.com/sponsors/hanami">GitHub Sponsors</a>,
        as a business or an individual.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">Become a business sponsor</h2>

      <p class="mb-4">As a Hanakai business sponsor, you'll receive several benefits:</p>

      <ul class="space-y-1 mb-4">
        <li>Private chat with Hanakai maintainers</li>
        <li>Priority attention on issues or requests</li>
        <li>Your logo and link on our website</li>
        <li>Shoutouts on social media and in release announcements</li>
      </ul>

      <p>Most important of all, you'll be creating a healthy and diverse future for Ruby.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">Business tiers</h2>

      <div class="space-y-8">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-1">Platinum</h3>
          <p class="font-medium mb-3">$12,000/year</p>
          <ul class="space-y-1">
            <li>Large logo on Hanakai home page</li>
            <li>Logo in the footer of all Hanakai pages, including docs</li>
            <li>Acknowledgement in major and minor release announcements</li>
            <li>Access to private chat</li>
            <li>Priority for issues &amp; requests</li>
            <li>Twice-yearly call with Tim</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-1">Gold</h3>
          <p class="font-medium mb-3">$6,000/year</p>
          <ul class="space-y-1">
            <li>Medium logo on Hanakai home page</li>
            <li>Acknowledgement in major release announcements</li>
            <li>Access to private chat</li>
            <li>Priority for issues &amp; requests</li>
            <li>Yearly call with Tim</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-1">Silver</h3>
          <p class="font-medium mb-3">$3,000/year</p>
          <ul class="space-y-1">
            <li>Small logo on Hanakai home page</li>
            <li>Acknowledgement in major release announcements</li>
            <li>Access to private chat</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="mt-6">
        Please <a href="mailto:sponsor@hanakai.org">reach out</a> if you want
        to discuss any aspect of business sponsorship.
      </p>

      <p class="mt-4">
        <a href="http://opencollective.com/hanami">Become a business sponsor</a>
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">You're in good company</h2>

      <p class="mb-8">
        Thank you to these amazing business sponsors! We'd love to see you join them.
      </p>

      <div class="space-y-6 mb-10">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">Platinum</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Sidekiq</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">Gold</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-1">
            <li>Honeybadger</li>
            <li>FastRuby.io</li>
            <li>AppSignal</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">Silver</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Brandon Weaver</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-6">Hear from our sponsors</h3>

      <div class="space-y-8">
        <blockquote>
          <p>
            Ruby has a problem: it's mostly a monoculture around Rails. Merb and
            Sinatra provided valuable app framework options in the past, I believe
            we need new options for the future.
          </p>
          <p>
            Mike Perham<br>
            Sidekiq
          </p>
        </blockquote>

        <blockquote>
          <p>
            In Ruby diversity is our greatest strength, whether that be the
            people, the ideas, or the technologies we use. Ruby is not just one
            framework, nor is it just one person, it is a community of passionate
            people pushing the boundaries of what's possible not just as
            individuals, but as a collective. I am happy to continue to fund
            efforts building upon that vision of the future.
          </p>
          <p>Brandon Weaver</p>
        </blockquote>

        <blockquote>
          <p>
            Honeybadger has been monitoring Ruby apps since 2012, and we've
            always believed in giving back to the open source community that made
            our business possible. We're proud to sponsor a framework and team
            that is working to make Ruby better for everyone. Hanami is leading
            the way.
          </p>
          <p>
            Joshua Wood<br>
            Honeybadger
          </p>
        </blockquote>

        <blockquote>
          <p>
            At FastRuby we believe in the value of diverse and inclusive
            communities. With our yearly contribution to Hanami we are investing
            in a framework that brings positive change to our beloved Ruby
            ecosystem. We envision a future where projects like Hanami, Roda,
            Sinatra, Cuba, and Padrino push the boundaries of what's possible in
            Ruby.
          </p>
          <p>
            Ernesto Tagwerker<br>
            FastRuby
          </p>
        </blockquote>

        <blockquote>
          <p>
            At AppSignal, we believe in sustainable open-source software and are
            happy to contribute to Hanami's development by enabling others to
            continue the great work they do. In turn, this allows us to keep
            providing APM services that smoothly integrate with Hanami. Everybody
            wins.
          </p>
          <p>
            Roy Tomeij<br>
            AppSignal
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">Become an individual sponsor</h2>

      <p class="mb-4">We welcome your support as Ruby community members! You can:</p>

      <ul class="space-y-2">
        <li>
          Become an individual sponsor. Support Hanakai through
          <a href="https://opencollective.com/hanami">Open Collective</a> or
          <a href="https://github.com/sponsors/hanami">GitHub Sponsors</a>
          at whatever amount you choose.
        </li>
        <li>Bring this pitch to the financial decision-makers at your workplace.</li>
        <li>
          Share our work on social media. Big things are happening for Hanakai
          and we want everyone to know.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <aside>
      <p>
        Thank you for your support! It means the world to us.
      </p>

      <p>
        If you have any questions, I'd love to hear from you. Please feel free to
        contact me directly.
      </p>

      <p>— Tim</p>
    </aside>
  </div>
</div>
